(42, 7, 49, 42, 5, 20, 21, 'forgiveth sins also', 'Forgiveness of Sins', 'Both passages emphasize the question of who has the authority to forgive sins. In Luke 7:49, the guests question Jesus'' ability to forgive, paralleling the scribes'' reasoning in Luke 5:21 about blasphemy and divine authority.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 49, 40, 9, 3, 3, 'forgiveth sins also', 'Responses to Forgiveness Claims', 'Both passages emphasize the internal questioning of Jesus'' authority to forgive sins. In Luke, the guests wonder, ''Who is this that forgiveth sins also?'' while in Matthew, the scribes accuse him of blasphemy, indicating their disbelief in his claim to forgive.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 49, 41, 2, 7, 7, 'forgiveth sins also', 'Forgiveness of Sins', 'Both passages emphasize the authority to forgive sins, raising questions about the identity of Jesus. The reactions of those present highlight the belief that only God can forgive sins.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
