(42, 8, 1, 45, 10, 15, 15, 'glad tidings', 'Connection of Preaching Glad Tidings', 'This connection highlights the theme of preaching the ''glad tidings'' of the kingdom of God. Both passages emphasize the importance of those who proclaim the gospel and the beauty of their mission.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 1, 40, 9, 35, 35, NULL, 'Preaching the Kingdom of God', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' ministry of preaching the gospel of the kingdom and His travels through cities and villages. They highlight His role in teaching and healing, showcasing the comprehensive nature of His mission.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 1, 44, 10, 38, 38, NULL, 'Connection of Jesus'' Ministry', 'This connection highlights the active ministry of Jesus as he ''went about doing good'' and ''preaching... the glad tidings of the kingdom of God.'' Both passages emphasize Jesus'' role in healing and spreading the message of God''s kingdom.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 1, 44, 13, 32, 32, 'glad tidings', 'Connection of Glad Tidings', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of ''glad tidings,'' linking the proclamation of the kingdom of God in Luke to the declaration of promises in Acts. This connection highlights the continuity of the message throughout the early Christian movement.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 1, 23, 61, 1, 3, 'glad tidings of the kingdom of God', 'Connection of Good Tidings', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of preaching good tidings. Luke 8:1 mentions ''the glad tidings of the kingdom of God,'' while Isaiah 61:1 speaks of ''good tidings unto the meek.'' This connection highlights the continuity of the message of hope and liberation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 1, 41, 1, 39, 39, 'preaching and shewing the glad tidings', 'Preaching and Ministry Activities', 'Both passages emphasize the act of preaching as a central activity of Jesus. Luke highlights Jesus preaching the glad tidings of the kingdom, while Mark notes his preaching in synagogues throughout Galilee.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 2, 41, 16, 9, 9, 'out of whom went seven devils', 'Connection of Mary Magdalene''s Healing', 'Both passages emphasize Mary Magdalene, highlighting her healing from seven devils. This connection underscores her significance in the narrative of Jesus'' ministry and resurrection.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 2, 40, 27, 55, 56, 'Mary called Magdalene', 'Women Following Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the role of women in Jesus'' ministry. Luke 8:2 mentions Mary Magdalene as a follower who was healed, while Matthew 27:55-56 identifies her among those ministering to Jesus.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 2, 41, 15, 40, 41, 'Mary called Magdalene', 'Women Following Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of women who were significant in Jesus'' ministry. Mary Magdalene is specifically mentioned in both, highlighting her role as a devoted follower after being healed.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 2, 43, 19, 25, 25, 'Mary called Magdalene', 'Connection of Mary Magdalene', 'Both passages emphasize Mary Magdalene''s presence in significant moments. In Luke, she is identified as having been healed, while in John, she stands by the cross of Jesus, highlighting her importance in the narrative.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 2, 42, 23, 27, 27, 'women, which had been healed', 'Women Following Jesus', 'This connection highlights the presence of women in both passages. In Luke 8:2, women who were healed follow Jesus, while in Luke 23:27, women are depicted as lamenting him, indicating their ongoing support and emotional response to his ministry.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 2, 42, 23, 49, 49, NULL, 'Women Following Jesus', 'This connection highlights the presence of women in both passages. In Luke 8:2, women like Mary Magdalene are mentioned as followers of Jesus, while Luke 23:49 notes that women who followed him from Galilee were present at his crucifixion.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 2, 44, 1, 14, 14, NULL, 'Role of Women in Early Church', 'This connection highlights the presence of women in both passages. In Luke, Mary Magdalene is mentioned among those healed, while Acts emphasizes women participating in prayer with the apostles.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 3, 43, 4, 46, 53, NULL, 'Healing and Faith Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of healing through faith. In Luke, the women support Jesus, while in John, the nobleman believes in Jesus'' word for his son''s healing.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 3, 44, 9, 36, 39, 'ministered unto him of their substance', 'Women in Ministry and Service', 'Both passages emphasize the role of women who serve and support others through good works. Joanna and Susanna in Luke provide for Jesus, while Tabitha (Dorcas) in Acts is noted for her almsdeeds and service to widows.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 3, 47, 8, 9, 9, 'ministered unto him of their substance', 'Connection of Riches and Poverty', 'This connection highlights the theme of material support and sacrifice. In Luke 8:3, those who ministered to Jesus did so from their substance, reflecting a form of poverty in service. Similarly, 2 Corinthians 8:9 emphasizes Jesus'' choice to become poor for others'' benefit, linking the concepts of wealth and sacrifice.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 3, 50, 4, 22, 22, 'ministered unto him of their substance', 'Support from Wealthy Followers', 'This connection highlights the theme of support from influential individuals. Both passages mention individuals associated with prominent figures, indicating a network of support for the ministry.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
